{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"A plugin whose manifest is missing a required field is rejected before any code from that plugin is executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure is at a module boundary: manifest validation must gate module import/execution. A unit test of validation logic alone can miss regressions where the loader still imports plugin code. No subprocess/network/real external API is required, so System is not needed; no AI dependency.","test_description":"Create a temporary plugin directory with one plugin containing an invalid `manifest.json` (missing a required field) and an entry module with a visible side effect (for example, writing a marker file or mutating shared state at import time). Run the real loader against that directory and assert: (1) the plugin is rejected with a validation error, and (2) the side effect never occurred, proving no plugin code executed.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.77,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When plugin A declares a dependency on plugin B, plugin B's `onLoad` hook is called before plugin A's.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This behavior depends on interaction between dependency resolution and lifecycle invocation across multiple plugins. A pure unit test of topological sort is insufficient to catch wiring bugs in actual load/hook sequencing. No real subprocess/network/external API is needed.","test_description":"Set up plugins `A` and `B` where `A` depends on `B`. Each `onLoad` appends its name to a shared call log. Run the loader and assert the log order is exactly `['B','A']` (or that `B` appears before `A` if others exist).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.82,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"When two plugins each declare a dependency on the other, the loader reports the cycle and loads neither.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Cycle detection plus load suppression spans resolver and loader execution paths. A unit test of cycle detection alone can miss a real failure where hooks still run despite detected cycles. Higher levels are disqualified because behavior text is limited to local dependency metadata/loader behavior, with no subprocess/network/AI steps.","test_description":"Create plugins `A` and `B` with mutual dependencies (`A -> B`, `B -> A`) and `onLoad` hooks that record execution if called. Run the loader and assert: (1) a cycle error/report is emitted, and (2) neither `A` nor `B` `onLoad` executed.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.11,"Integration":0.84,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A plugin's `onLoad` hook is only invoked after the plugin's entry module has been imported and executed.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is ordering between module import execution and lifecycle hook call. This requires real wiring of loader + module import + hook dispatch, not just one function. System is not required because this can be reproduced in-process with local filesystem fixtures; no external OS/subprocess/network dependency beyond normal module loading.","test_description":"Create a plugin whose entry module sets `initialized = true` as an import-time side effect, and whose `onLoad` asserts/records that `initialized` is already true. Run loader and assert `onLoad` is reached only after import side effect is present (and fails if order is wrong).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When a plugin throws an error during its `onLoad` hook, the loader continues initializing the remaining plugins that do not depend on it.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This tests cross-module orchestration: error isolation, dependency-aware skip/continue behavior, and continued lifecycle execution for unaffected plugins. Unit tests of error handling in one function may miss end-to-end scheduling behavior. No real network/subprocess/AI dependency is present.","test_description":"Create plugin `A` whose `onLoad` throws, plugin `C` with no dependency on `A`, and plugin `D` that depends on `A`. Run loader and assert: (1) `A` failure is reported, (2) `C` still loads successfully, and (3) `D` is not initialized due to dependency on failed `A`.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.09,"Integration":0.86,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
